### Data (Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International)

The eval cases (`eval/cases/`), grader meta-prompts (`eval/graders/`),
SME-labeled gold examples (`eval/validation/`), and run results
(`eval/results/`) are released under CC-BY-4.0:

https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

You are free to share and adapt this material for any purpose, including
commercial, provided you give appropriate credit, link to the license, and
indicate if changes were made.

### Policy corpus excerpts (`data/policy_corpus/`)

Federal and state policy documents pulled from public sources (eCFR,
NYS OTDA, NYC HRA) are reproduced under fair use for the purpose of
evaluation grounding. Original sources retain their original status as
public records. Each file's `meta.yaml` records the source URL and the
date pulled.
